Protection levels (advisory):
- PROTECTED: do not change without explicit approval
- GUARDED: ask before altering signatures or logic shape
- INFO: context-only notes
- TEST: test-only code
- DEBUG: temporary diagnostics
- CRITICAL: business logic; keep edits minimal and well-tested

Commands (advisory markers you can add to comments):
- !cp (PROTECTED)
- !cg (GUARDED)
- !ci (INFO)
- !ct (TEST)
- !cd (DEBUG)
- !cc (CRITICAL)

Respect these markers if found in code. When removing a marker, state the rationale in the review/commit body.